data.name: Spicy Vegetable Stir-Fry with Tofu
data.quickTastyDescription: A quick and vibrant stir-fry bursting with flavor and packed with nutrients!
detailedCookingInstructions: Press the tofu to remove excess moisture, then cut it into cubes.
Heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add the tofu cubes and fry until golden and crispy on all sides, about 5-7 minutes. Remove and set aside.
In the same skillet, add garlic and ginger, saut√© for 1 minute until fragrant.
Add broccoli, bell pepper, and carrot, stir-frying for about 3-4 minutes until vegetables are tender yet crisp.
Return the tofu to the skillet, add soy sauce and chili paste, and stir to combine everything well. Cook for an additional 2 minutes.
Serve hot, garnished with sesame seeds if desired.
data.modifiersForBase: Add tofu and spices for extra flavor and protein.
